  Game Rules

  Build a browser-based Memory (Concentration) card game for 2–4 players, played on a single screen with pass-and-play turns.

  - A standard 52-card deck is shuffled and laid face-down in a 4 × 13 grid.
  - On each turn, the active player flips two cards face-up. All players see them briefly, then both cards flip face-down again.
  - If the two cards share the same rank (e.g. two 7s), the active player claims the pair. It slides into their hand area and they take another
