⏺ ★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────
  The press-down-then-flip sequence is a two-stage animation chain — you need the press to complete before the flip starts. CSS alone can do
  this with animation-delay, but it's cleaner to trigger the flip via a transitionend event listener on the press animation. This ensures the
  timing stays correct even if the browser is under load and animations slow down.
